news.title: South Korea expects revenue from real estate tax to be three times higher in 2021
news.para: The government revised the law last year, increasing the holding tax rate for homeowners, as part of efforts to cool the country's red-hot real estate market. The changes took effect this year.

news.title: EFC leases 60,000 sq ft space in Hyderabad, 38,000 sq ft in Mumbai
news.para: Average rent in Hyderabad spaces will be Rs 5,500 per seat per month while in BKC it will be Rs 14,000 per seat per month.

news.title: Lifestyle International chairman buys residential plot in Bengaluru for Rs 15.2 crore
news.para: The property jointly owned by Lumba and his wife was purchased earlier by Madhuri Genomal, wife of Sunder Genomal- MD of Page Industries and her daughter, Pamela Kripalani.

news.title: Delhi government lifts ban on construction and demolition activities
news.para: Delhi's Air Quality Index (AQI) dropped to 303 on a scale of 500, down from 499 nearly a week ago, when a thick haze hung over the city of more than 200 million people. The current AQI levels still indicate "very poor" conditions, according to government monitoring agencies.

news.title: Over 18 crore revenue records digitised in Haryana
news.para: At the state-level and in all districts, 18.5 crore records have been scanned and digitized, which will be easily available at the click of a mouse.

news.title: True Habitat raises Rs 30 crore from CSL Finance
news.para: It will launch an affordable housing project having 650-700 apartments and 45,692 sq ft of commercial space on the acquired land parcel.

news.title: Goa: GIDC puts up 22 SEZ plots in Verna for e-auction
news.para: GIDC is offering plots ranging from 1,500 sqm to 45,000 sqm on long lease as it tries to fund its way out of the debt taken in May 2019 to repay five SEZ promoters.

news.title: Public hearing for expansion of Chennai metropolitan area in Chengalpet on Nov 25
news.para: Chengalpet district collector AR Rahul Nadh said that elected representatives, non-governmental organisations, representatives from commercial and industries sector and general public can participate in the meeting.

news.title: CIDCO to adopt Maharashtra unified DCR for rapid development of NAINA project
news.para: To prevent haphazard development around the Navi Mumbai International Airport, CIDCO has proposed the development of NAINA on 371 sq km of land from the Thane and Raigad districts.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM hands over keys of houses to PMAY beneficiaries
news.para: "Previous governments did not have any idea about how development works should be done for the poor. The poor did not get houses owing to lack of willpower. Our government provided houses to 45 lakh people," he claimed.

news.title: Aurangabad civic body's recovers Rs 69.8 crore property tax in FY22
news.para: Aparna Thete, in-charge of Aurangabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) tax-recovery, on Sunday said all defaulters including major ones should pay their dues at the earliest.

news.title: Chandigarh: Sector 29 homes to have house number indicator boards soon
news.para: Area councillor Shakti Parkash Devshali pushed the case on the demand of residents. The MC has decided to put up similar boards in the entire city.

news.title: No question of protecting anyone in BDA corruption: Karnataka CM
news.para: ​The Anti-Corruption Bureau (ACB), on Friday had raided the BDA office here and claimed to have unearthed irregularities and corruption by officials during acquisition and allotment of land in residential layouts.

news.title: IT department detects Rs 100-crore black income after raids on Gujarat group
news.para: "...incriminating evidences in the form of documents, diary notings and digital data showing earning of huge unaccounted income by the group and its investment in assets have been seized," the CBDT said in a statement.

news.title: Why insolvency cases are giving Noida & Greater Noida authorities a tough time
news.para: While the GNIDA is dealing with 21 cases of insolvency proceedings before the National Company Law Tribunal and the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal, the Noida Authority is party to 16 such resolution cases or appeals, at present.
